{"topicSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/CodeEditSourceEditor\/documentation\/CodeEditSourceEditor\/GutterView\/init(font:textColor:textView:delegate:)"],"title":"Initializers"},{"title":"Instance Properties","identifiers":["doc:\/\/CodeEditSourceEditor\/documentation\/CodeEditSourceEditor\/GutterView\/gutterWidth","doc:\/\/CodeEditSourceEditor\/documentation\/CodeEditSourceEditor\/GutterView\/isFlipped"]},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/CodeEditSourceEditor\/documentation\/CodeEditSourceEditor\/GutterView\/draw(_:)"],"title":"Instance Methods"}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/CodeEditSourceEditor\/documentation\/CodeEditSourceEditor\/GutterView","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"patch":0,"minor":3},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/CodeEditSourceEditor\/documentation\/CodeEditSourceEditor"]]},"kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The gutter view displays line numbers that match the text view’s line indexes."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"This view is used as a scroll view’s ruler view. It sits on top of the text view so text scrolls underneath the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"gutter if line wrapping is disabled."}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/codeeditsourceeditor\/gutterview"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"GutterView","kind":"identifier"}],"languages":["swift"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"anchor":"overview","level":2,"text":"Overview","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"If the gutter needs more space (when the number of digits in the numbers increases eg. adding a line after line 99),","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"it will notify it’s delegate via the "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/CodeEditSourceEditor\/documentation\/CodeEditSourceEditor\/GutterViewDelegate\/gutterViewWidthDidUpdate(newWidth:)"},{"type":"text","text":" method. In"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CodeEditSourceEditor"},{"text":", this notifies the ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/CodeEditSourceEditor\/documentation\/CodeEditSourceEditor\/TextViewController"},{"type":"text","text":", which in turn updates the textview’s edge insets"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to adjust for the new leading inset."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This view also listens for selection updates, and draws a selected background on selected lines to keep the illusion"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"that the gutter’s line numbers are inline with the line itself.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The gutter view has insets of it’s own that are relative to the widest line index. By default, these insets are 20px"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"leading, and 12px trailing. However, this view also has a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GutterView\/backgroundEdgeInsets"},{"text":" property, that pads","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"the rect that has a background drawn. This allows the text to be scrolled under the gutter view for 8px before being","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"overlapped by the gutter. It should help the textview keep the cursor visible if the user types while the cursor is"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"off the leading edge of the editor."}]}],"kind":"content"}],"relationshipsSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/CodeEditSourceEditor\/objc(cs)NSView"],"kind":"relationships","type":"inheritsFrom","title":"Inherits From"},{"type":"conformsTo","title":"Conforms To","kind":"relationships","identifiers":["doc:\/\/CodeEditSourceEditor\/objc(pl)NSAccessibilityElement","doc:\/\/CodeEd